cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CC 

This paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the capacity of a channel with additive Gaussian noise and multiple non-causally known Gaussian state sequences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves statistical modeling and analysis of the state sequences, which could fall under cs.MM (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of pre-coding and decoding techniques suggests a possible fit with cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper deals with capacity bounds and outer bounds, which could be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
